      "content": "\n<figure data-orig-width=\"2000\" data-orig-height=\"2000\" class=\"tmblr-full\"><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/4e2bb8263064060be5c1d6a5ddd3b858/80c56c7199f09b14-02/s540x810/6d14fe7efaf798aee1442be29ff051791443f465.jpg\" alt=\"image\" data-orig-width=\"2000\" data-orig-height=\"2000\"></figure><p>I hate keeping secrets and this was a hard one. Ever since my friend Robbie told me about this band I couldn’t stop listening to them. They brought me back to the late 2000s when I’d go to show four times a week and the heavier a band was, the better. This is for fans of Ed Gein, Maruta, Daughters and the like. </p>\n<p><b>I am pleased to welcome THIN to the Twelve Gauge family. </b></p>\n<p><b>Thin is a 3-piece mathgrind band from New York City</b> that formed in the spring of 2019. The band delivers a chaotic, aggressive, and unhinged barrage of blasting drums, off-kilter grooves, and slashing guitars. Thin released their debut LP, dawn, on April 20, 2020, which Decibel Magazine described as a “cover-to-cover assault on the brain.” Pressed to cassette in the US and Europe (Lower Class Kids Records), dawn is seeing new life in the form of a one-sided 12”LP, along with a repress of the tape, on Twelve Gauge Records. For fans of Ed Gein, Maruta, and Daughters.<br></p>\n<p><b>Tomorrow we release a 12″LP and Cassette combo</b> that’s in hands and ready to ship, along with an awesome shirt by Sean Leary.<br></p>\n<p>You can stream the album in it’s entirety <a href=\"https://twelvegauge.bandcamp.com/album/dawn\">here</a> and pick up the following items on <a href=\"http://store.tgrex.com/\">our webstore</a> starting tomorrow (Friday July 24) at Noon Eastern time:<br></p>\n<figure data-orig-width=\"1080\" data-orig-height=\"1078\" class=\"tmblr-full\"><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/c6ff3c549c093e89aaa9855877233684/80c56c7199f09b14-37/s540x810/79f02ae1875260f50deb86bb947b41c09f023bd6.png\" alt=\"image\" data-orig-width=\"1080\" data-orig-height=\"1078\"></figure>\n",
